  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The chronic success rate, defined as freedom from any atrial tachyarrhythmias will increase
      from 35% to 60% by ablation of complex fragmented atrial electrograms potentials in addition
      to pulmonary vein isolation (PVI) as compared to PVI alone in patients with long-standing
      persistent AF.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
